22:06.770 --> 22:12.518
special about, as you look back, what was special 
about those chickens? though you were praising

22:12.802 --> 22:21.553
the Corps, what did those first two or three years 
do to you and your personality that were

22:12.802 --> 22:21.553
important? Well, I think what the Corps does is it 
teaches you, it operates on the theory of in order

22:22.754 --> 22:35.370
to be a leader, you've got to know what it feels like 
to be led. And I think that's what I think that right

22:37.186 --> 22:39.309
there is what makes it special. All the other stuff 
is kind of side benefits. You get to make long

22:41.432 --> 22:45.939
lasting friends that are going to be your friends 
forever and ever. And the closeness and the

22:45.999 --> 22:51.948
camaraderie in the spirit. I think the Corps has a 
special role. If you had asked me back then, if you

22:54.733 --> 23:00.882
had told me in 1972 on the day that I graduated in May 
that, you know, this school is going to be 50,000

23:01.402 --> 23:10.271
kids and 2,000 or less are going to be in the core. 
You think they'll still stand up for football

23:10.892 --> 23:12.774
games? You think they'll still do all, have 
midnight yell practice? I said, in no way in the

23:15.897 --> 23:18.240
world that would exist. And the fact that that is 
just as strong or stronger than it ever has been

23:20.202 --> 23:30.953
before, I think is a testament to the kind of kids 
that come here, but I think it also is a testament to

23:20.202 --> 23:30.953
the core maybe kind of keeps the fire stoked and and 
stuff and as part of it uh academics uh you you know

