Courses and or instructors or advisors? My 
favorite political science professor was Gary

24:10.400 --> 24:13.845
Halter. I thought he was really good. I liked his 
courses a lot. I didn't get into his until I was into

24:19.194 --> 24:24.362
my sophomore year and stuff like that. But my best 
course, funny you should ask this, that I did the

24:25.152 --> 24:33.522
worst in was American history. And we had this 
professor that had this unbelievable

24:34.103 --> 24:41.232
photographic memory of the Civil War. And it was so 
fascinating. And I'm not saying this because this

24:43.295 --> 24:45.878
professor is in the room. But it was so fascinating 
that I never took a note. I sat in the back of the

24:49.402 --> 24:50.664
class. I remember that class specifically. I sat 
in the back of that class. just mesmerized at how in

24:54.194 --> 25:00.842
the hell does this guy remember the dates and stuff 
of all this stuff. And we would look at each other

25:00.862 --> 25:05.628
and we refought the Civil War right there in that. 
And I never had any of that in high school, you know.

25:09.634 --> 25:12.918
And that was the best course I took at A&M. It really 
was high school. And there's lots of kids that will

25:14.340 --> 25:17.143
say the same thing. Best course I took. But I think I 
got a D in it. I never took a note and I could not

25:23.405 --> 25:28.398
remember those damn dates that you were always 
asking for on the test.

